WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.500
[Music]

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.000
You can generate captions within Studio,

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.500
or upload your own Studio file.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:13.500
If you want to request captions for your media,

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:15.500
select Captions,

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:18.000
and then choose the language spoken in the media
in the drop-down box.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:20.500
Select the Request button.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.500
The caption request will then be queued.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:26.500
Once the captions has been loaded,

00:00:26.500 --> 00:00:28.500
a Review and Publish button will appear.

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:31.000
Select the button to proofread
the caption transcript's.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.500
The text will align with timing markers

00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:36.500
on the left-hand side.

00:00:36.500 --> 00:00:39.500
You can click the text and make edits as neccessary,

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:43.000
then publish your revisions.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:45.500
You can also choose to upload your own caption file.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.500
The most common type is an SRT file,

00:00:48.500 --> 00:00:50.500
but Studio also supports VTT files,

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:53.000
which are more user-friendly for mobile devices.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:55.500
If you have an SRT or VTT file to upload,

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.500
then select the language to the right
in the Upload section.

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:03.500
Anyone viewing the Studio media can then
turn captions on

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:05.500
by selecting the CC button
in the media player bar.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.500
Choose from the list of languages provided.

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:24
The captions will appear at the top
of the media player. Thanks for watching is displayed! Presented by Sean Nufer HOW TO CANVAS.COM, Subscribe Here!
